quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,60,"He is the One Who calls back your souls by night and knows what you do by day, then revives you daily to complete your appointed term. To Him is your ˹ultimate˺ return, then He will inform you of what you used to do"
  6,61,"He reigns supreme over all of His creation, and sends recording-angels, watching over you. When death comes to any of you, Our angels take their soul, never neglecting this duty"
  6,62,Then they are ˹all˺ returned to God—their True Master. Judgment is His ˹alone˺. And He is the Swiftest Reckoner
  6,63,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Who rescues you from the darkest times on land and at sea? He ˹alone˺ you call upon with humility, openly and secretly: “If You rescue us from this, we will be ever grateful.”"
  6,64,"Say, “˹Only˺ God rescues you from this and any other distress, yet you associate others with Him ˹in worship˺.”"
  6,65,"Say, “He ˹alone˺ has the power to unleash upon you a torment from above or below you or split you into ˹conflicting˺ factions and make you taste the violence of one another.” See how We vary the signs, so perhaps they will comprehend"
  6,66,"Still your people ˹O Prophet˺ have rejected this ˹Quran˺, although it is the truth. Say, “I am not a keeper over you.”"
  6,67,Every ˹destined˺ matter has a ˹set˺ time to transpire. And you will soon come to know
  6,68,"And when you come across those who ridicule Our revelations, do not sit with them unless they engage in a different topic. Should Satan make you forget, then once you remember, do not ˹continue to˺ sit with the wrongdoing people"